+# Step-6 Freeze Keeps Repaired Template Defect And Repaired Leakage As Two Distinct Promoted Objects
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` Step-6 verdict with `INFERRED` no-collapse synthesis
+
+The completed Step-6 exploration does not narrow the post-repair shortlist
+further.
+It freezes repaired `Template-Defect Near-Closure` and repaired
+`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` as two distinct promoted objects on the
+same canonical packet ledger.
+
+The two survivors stay promoted unchanged rather than being repackaged.
+`Template-Defect Near-Closure` still acts on
+`(Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)` as the theorem-facing role-template gate, while
+`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` still acts on
+`(L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)` as the
+obstruction-facing classwise admissibility gate.
+Step 5 only removed slack from their admissibility sheets; it did not change
+the packet class, fixed window, canonical sheet, spectator partition, or
+underlying interaction currency.
+
+The local record does not prove a dominance relation in either direction.
+Passing `G_tmpl` is not shown to force `G_leak`, passing `G_leak` is not
+shown to force `G_tmpl`, and the shared outcomes on
+`F_SS(1/12)`, `F_SL(1/16)`, and `F_DT(delta, eta)` are only dossier-level
+co-orientation rather than an equivalence theorem.
+
+Step 6 therefore rejects both collapse paths.
+Do not collapse everything into leakage.
+Do not collapse everything into template defect.
+Do not replace the pair by a conjunction object `G_tmpl + G_leak`, because
+that would manufacture a stronger compound gate not already earned on the
+frozen ledger.
+
+The Step-5 rejects also stay background only.
+`pre-trigger delay filter` remains
+`not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`, and
+`next-stage transfer-start filter` remains `not well-defined`, so neither
+discarded itinerary fragment is reintroduced as a soft third downstream
+object.
+
